        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 6:55PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 653 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles southwest of Clinton to Howellsville to
near Elrod. Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and weakened trees.
Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lumberton, Elizabethtown, Pembroke, Bladenboro, Bladen Community
College, Ammon, Butters, Hestertown, Robeson Community College, White
Oak, Elrod, Smiths, Howellsville, Raemon, Duart, Tolarsville,
Abbottsburg, Lisbon, Lagoon, and Elkton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building until the storm passes.</instruction>
